Rating: 3
We totally enjoyed this recipe. I am not a lover of fennel but it transformed this dessert into a foreign delight. I followed the recipe as written and thought the filling and phyllo was perfect. The colors were beautiful and the dish was extremely attractive.

Rating: 3
The orange cream was a bit too thin, but otherwise delicious!

Rating: 4
I made this for New Year's Eve dinner and it was a big hit. I used a chinese ten spice instead of the recommended five spice. The spice combined with the sugar and butter created a very complex yet tasty combination of flavors in the phylo. Be forwarned; while this dessert appears light and creamy, it is definitely rich. I would recommend using a low fat cream cheese instead to cut down on the heaviness of the filling.